<paragraph pageId="23" pageNumber="346">Female (IBSP 12111). Typical general coloration of genus, lateral sides of abdomen with inconspicuous white spots. Median plate of epigyne almost as wide as long, becoming wider posteriorly. Lateral plates almost completely covered by median plate which presents a little knob posteriorly(Fig. 42). Medianly bulged copulatory ducts enter the wide apart spermathecae interiorly by a strong curve (Fig. 43). Chelicerae with 3 promarginal and 3 retromarginal teeth.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="23" pageNumber="346">Measurements. Total length 15.30. Prosoma 7.5 long 5.7 wide, Clypeus 0.32. Eye diameters and interdistances: AME 0.38, ALE 0.26, PME 0.4, PLE 0.42; AME-AME 0.2, AME-ALE 0.32, PME-PME 0.2, PME-PLE 0.4, ALE-PLE 0.22, AME-PME 0.14, MOQ length 1.0, front width 0.92, back width 1.06. Epigyne: 2.8 long, 2.6 wide.</paragraph>
